ProMED

******
[4] Puerto Rico
Date: Wed 29 Jun 2022
Source: Infobae [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2022/06/29/puerto-rico-confirma-el-primer-caso-de-viruela-del-mono-en-la-isla-2/


This Wednesday [29 Jun 2022], the Puerto Rico Health Department confirmed the 1st case of monkeypox on the Island and requested that the population be alert in order to halt any transmission chain.

The patient remains in isolation in his home, in stable condition according to the announcement by the Health Department.

"This is the moment when we all must be alert to the clinical symptoms and the epidemiological criteria of the virus in order for us to prevent infections and halt whatever transmission chain," the Secretary of Health, Carlos Mellado López, said.

This 1st case was identified through the surveillance system for required notification of diseases, that coordinated sample taking. The Health Department established an Epidemiological Surveillance Guide for Monkeypox at the beginning of June [2022] that included information for diagnosis and management of cases for healthcare providers and health institutions.

Before the 1st case was confirmed, the main health official, Melissa Marzán Rodríguez, emphasized that "it is important that people who present with symptoms associated [with monkeypox] consult with your healthcare provider immediately."

--
