[7] Netherlands: child
Date: Tue 28 Jun 2022
Source: AD [in Dutch, machine trans., edited]
https://www.ad.nl/binnenland/voor-het-eerst-apenpokkenvirus-vastgesteld-bij-een-kind~a6d6ee81/


The monkeypox virus has been diagnosed in a child in the Netherlands for the 1st time. The child is of primary school age, says a spokeswoman for the National Institute for Public Health and the Environment (RIVM). It is not yet known how the child contracted the virus.

For privacy reasons, the spokeswoman cannot say how the child is doing now. Monkeypox has now been diagnosed in 257 people in the Netherlands, 46 more than last Friday [24 Jun 2022]. Except for this child, in all cases it concerns men who have sex with men.

