Communicated by:
Mary Marshall
<mjm2020@googlemail.com>

[A 16 Jun 2022 published report stated that the estimate of the mean incubation period of monkeypox in this outbreak was 8.5 days, in line with the typical values for complex, invasive exposure. Among the analysed cases in this outbreak and using this best-fitting (lognormal) distribution, the mean incubation period of monkeypox was estimated to be 8.5 days (95% credible intervals: 6.6-10.9 days), with the 5th percentile of 4.2 days and the 95th percentile of 17.3 days.

This result is supported by the epidemiological observation that all notified cases currently reported in the Netherlands are MSM, mostly with lesions in the anal and genital regions. Direct contact between respective broken skin or mucous membranes during sexual activity might be the most likely route of transmission among cases reported in the current outbreak. (https://www.eurosurveillance.org/content/10.2807/1560-7917.ES.2022.27.24.2200448). - Mod.TY]

