[9] Africa
Date: Mon 27 Jun 2022
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/monkeypox-in-africa-1715-cases-73-deaths-in-2022-to-date-according-to-african-cdc-85163/


Since the beginning of 2022, 1715 cases (1636 suspected; 79 confirmed) and 73 deaths (CFR: 4.3%) of monkeypox have been reported from 8 endemic and 2 non-endemic African Union (AU) Member States (MS), according to the African CDC today [27 Jun 2022].

This includes Benin (3 cases, 0 deaths), Cameroon (28, 2), Central African Republic (17, 2), Republic of Congo (7, 3), Democratic Republic of the Congo (1439, 67), Ghana (12, 0), Nigeria (162 suspected, 41 confirmed, 1 death) and South Africa (1, 0), according to World Health Organization data (numbers differ slightly from Africa CDC numbers).

During the period of the COVID-19 pandemic (February 2020 to 27 Jun 2022), Africa has documented 12 141 cases and 363 deaths (CFR 3%) of monkeypox. The number of cases has continued to rise on the continent.

